cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or the COSMIC-ALLOW protocol, please cite it as below."
title: "Cosmic CLI: Fail-Closed Governance for Fail-Open AI Coding-Agent Cockpits (COSMIC-ALLOW RFC v1.1)"
abstract: >-
  A fail-closed proof-of-allow gate that mounts under the fail-open PreToolUse
  hook systems of AI coding cockpits (Claude Code, Grok Build). Deny is the
  ground state; a gate authorizes an action only by emitting the exact sentinel
  "COSMIC-ALLOW v1 <nonce>" as its entire standard output. Enforcement is
  layered: a kernel sandbox floor (provisioned by default, verified at launch),
  a privilege ranking, and command classification as defense in depth.
